reviewText: cheesey movie
This movie had bad acting, horrible quality of film and the plot was terrible!
One of the worst movies ever made. The acting was horrible! What a waste of an hour and a half of my life!

In 2017 a virus kills much of LA. Somehow the area is isolated without the virus getting out. A team is sent in to find a doctor who has a cure. However the cure is being sold to big Pharma by an individual within the government.

Plot was ill conceived. Acting was bad. Characters were made lame by dialogue. Soundtrack was made for TV quality. Bad editing.
Keeps cutting from this scene to that way too quickly. Junk acting. Don't waste your time with this movie.
Junk Movie.

How do you give no stars? This was the worse movie, I think I have ever seen. The acting is beyond awful, the only one who could act was the dog. I couldn't even finish watching the movie it was so bad. Save your money and your time, and your sanity.

The worst.  The worst acting, dialogue, spfx (there was none), they didn't show any zombies other than a blur running across the screen.  Awful, awful.  Did I mention the worst acting ever?  Not even close to the "quality" of Quarantine 1 and 2.  I actually enjoyed the earlier Quarantine movies as well as the REC movies.  But this was definitely an ignominious ending for the series.  And I really wanted to like it!  <sigh>
Scary

Not the worst zombie film on prime, but definitely in the bottom 20 percentile. Casting was just bizzare - an Asian woman as the commander of JSOC?  Who cares about reality when you can have diversity right? Asian women make up less the 2% of the officer's corps in the US Military and exactly NONE of the special operations command because - special ops is male only! But OK, not only do we have a woman running JSOC we have a corrupt woman who is trying to sell the zombie virus to Big Pharma. I cant understand why big pharma would WANT a zombie virus you know since zombies don't buy Viagra and Rogaine but whatever...  This is just "full of tropes" - crooked woman general who is like the asian cruella deville, steely eyed commando, asian film maker kid, 12 year old asian girl who looks 35, bumbling dufus, the ditzy girlfriend, a german scientist, and the evil escaped convict. Oh yeah and the bumbling govt agents who get pepper sprayed and evaded by a 12 year old.  Its like OK lets throw all the  overused cliches in a bag, and then pick them out at random.  Not good.
Not worth the rental fee or the time watching it. Acting bad and filming is horrible. The ending is the worse.
